Gnathosoma (
Figs. 19, 20
). Chaetotaxy and structure of palps (
Fig. 19
) and chelicerae (
Fig. 20
) as in
C. gordeevae
sp. nov.
Dorsal seta of basifemur filiform. The latter is more thin than dorsal setae on genu and telofemur. Apophysis of telofemur cone-like, with pointed apex, situated distally on the segment. Ventral surface of hypognathum with numerous papillae, coxal part with internal apodemes which form oval-shaped cells.

